<h3>Question 12</h3>
<div><p><p>State features of normal distribution. In a photographic process, the developing time of prints as a random variable having normal distribution with mean of 18.25 seconds with standard deviation 0.34 seconds. Find the probability that at least 17.64 seconds to develop one of the prints.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p><strong>Features of Normal Distribution:</strong></p>
<p>The normal distribution, also known as the Gaussian distribution or bell curve, is a continuous probability distribution that is characterized by several key features:</p>
<ol style="list-style-type:decimal;">
<li><strong>Symmetry:</strong> The normal distribution is symmetric about its mean (μ). The mean, median, and mode are all equal and located at the center of the distribution.</li>
<li><strong>Bell-Shaped Curve:</strong> The probability density function (PDF) of the normal distribution forms a bell-shaped curve, with the highest point at the mean and tails that extend infinitely in both directions.</li>
<li><strong>Unimodal:</strong> The normal distribution is unimodal, meaning it has a single peak.</li>
<li><strong>Parameters:</strong> The distribution is defined by two parameters: the mean (μ) and the standard deviation (σ). The mean determines the center of the distribution, while the standard deviation controls the spread or dispersion of the data. The larger the standard deviation, the wider the distribution.</li>
<li><strong>68-95-99.7 Rule:</strong> In a normal distribution:
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Approximately 68% of the data falls within one standard deviation of the mean.</li>
<li>Approximately 95% of the data falls within two standard deviations of the mean.</li>
<li>Approximately 99.7% of the data falls within three standard deviations of the mean.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Continuous:</strong> The normal distribution is defined for all real numbers, and it is a continuous distribution.</li>
</ol>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-25131" src="https://hamrocsit.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/SmartSelect_20230922_182945_CamScanner.jpg" alt="" width="913" height="606"></p>
</div>
<h3>Question 13</h3>
<div><p><p>Define random variable. If X is the number of points rolled with a balanced die, find E(X) and variance of X. Also find the expected value of random variable g(Y)=2X²+1.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p><strong>Random Variable:</strong> A random variable is a mathematical function or mapping that assigns numerical values to the outcomes of a random experiment or process. It represents a quantity whose value depends on chance or randomness. In other words, it&#8217;s a variable that can take on different values based on the outcomes of a random event.</p>
